T1  - Subordinates' Characteristics, Supervisors' Ratings, And Decisions To Discuss Appraisal Results
AU  - Feild, Hubert S.
AU  - Holley, William H.
Y1  - 1977/06/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255404
DO  - 10.5465/255404
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 315
EP  - 321
VL  - 20
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the results of a 1977 study pertaining to subordinate characteristics, supervisory ratings, and decisions to discuss appraisal results. The research indicated that voluntary discussion of rating results is associated with lower performance appraisals. It was found that the characteristics of the ratee can moderate the relationship between feedback of appraisal results and ratings given. The study also identified racial differences in the relationship between feedback and ratings.
AB  - The article discusses the results of a 1977 study pertaining to subordinate characteristics, supervisory ratings, and decisions to discuss appraisal results. The research indicated that voluntary discussion of rating results is associated with lower performance appraisals. It was found that the characteristics of the ratee can moderate the relationship between feedback of appraisal results and ratings given. The study also identified racial differences in the relationship between feedback and ratings.
