DA  - 1977/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255398
DO  - 10.5465/255398
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 251
EP  - 259
VL  - 20
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Both correlational and path analysis procedures were used to test the hypothesis that the initiation of structure-job satisfaction relationship would be mediated by occupational level. Separate analyses for supervisors (n = 26) and assemblers (n = 45) did not confirm the hypothesis. Support, in the null sense, was found for path-goal theory as distinct from the occupational level hypothesis.
AB  - Both correlational and path analysis procedures were used to test the hypothesis that the initiation of structure-job satisfaction relationship would be mediated by occupational level. Separate analyses for supervisors (n = 26) and assemblers (n = 45) did not confirm the hypothesis. Support, in the null sense, was found for path-goal theory as distinct from the occupational level hypothesis.
