PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examines the relative importance of job scope and individual differences in explaining job involvement. It further examines whether these variables have independent or interactive effects. Results indicate that job scope and three individual difference measures all have about equal importance in explaining the variance in job involvement.
AB  - This study examines the relative importance of job scope and individual differences in explaining job involvement. It further examines whether these variables have independent or interactive effects. Results indicate that job scope and three individual difference measures all have about equal importance in explaining the variance in job involvement.
